e":"1369–Zesnulý","1374–1416":"1374–1416","1398–1488":"1398–1488","1340–1375":"1340–1375","1344–1370":"1344–1370","before 1363":"před 1363","1363":"1363","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","1369":"1369","1488":"1488","1344":"1344","1366":"1366","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","about 1395":"okolo 1395","1416":"1416","Kintail, Highland, Scotland":"Kintail, Highland, Skotsko, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Scotland","Ross-shire, Scotland":"Ross-shire, Scotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland"},"da":{"1363–1416":"1363–1416","1366–Male":"1366–Afdød","1369–Male":"1369–Afdød","1374–1416":"1374–1416","1398–1488":"1398–1488","1340–1375":"1340–1375","1344–1370":"1344–1370","before 1363":"før 1363","1363":"1363","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","1369":"1369","1488":"1488","1344":"1344","1366":"1366","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","about 1395":"omkring 1395","1416":"1416","Kintail, Highland, Scotland":"Kintail, Highland, Skotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Skotland","Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Skotland","Ross-shire, Scotland":"Ross-shire, Skotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Skotland"},"nl":{"1363–1416":"1363–1416","1366–Male":"1366–Overleden","1369–Male":"1369–Overleden","1374–1416":"1374–1416","1398–1488":"1398–1488","1340–1375":"1340–1375","1344–1370":"1344–1370","before 1363":"vóór 1363","1363":"1363","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","1369":"1369","1488":"1488","1344":"1344","1366":"1366","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","about 1395":"circa 1395","1416":"1416","Kintail, Highland, Scotland":"Kintail, Highland, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland":"Schotland","Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Schotland","Ross-shire, Scotland":"Ross-shire, Schotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Schotland"},"en":{"1363–1416":"1363–1416","1366–Male":"1366–Deceased","1369–Male":"1369–Deceased","1374–1416":"1374–1416","1398–1488":"1398–1488","1340–1375":"1340–1375","1344–1370":"1344–1370","before 1363":"before 1363","1363":"1363","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","1369":"1369","1488":"1488","1344":"1344","1366":"1366","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","about 1395":"about 1395","1416":"1416","Kintail, Highland, Scotland":"Kintail, Highland, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Scotland","Ross-shire, Scotland":"Ross-shire, Scotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Mackenzie","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish:  see  McKenzie  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Kinsey","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Kynsey</i> (Old English <i>Cynesige</i> from <i>cyne-</i> ‘royal’ + <i>sige</i> ‘victory’).","Possibly also an Americanized form of Swiss German <b>Künzi</b> (see   Kuenzi  ).","History: The paternal grandfather of NJ and PA legislator John Kinsey (1693–1750) was one of the commissioners sent out from England in 1677 by the West Jersey proprietors to buy land from the Indians and to lay out a town. John was the leader of the Quaker party in the PA assembly and chief justice of the PA supreme court."]},{"name":"McKenzie","meanings":["Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Coinnich</b>, a patronymic from the personal name <i>Coinneach</i> meaning ‘comely’, Anglicized as <i>Kenneth</i>. Compare the Irish form   McKinney   2. The Scottish spelling with <i>-z-</i> indicates palatalization of the <i>-n-</i> (compare   Menzies  ).","History: This is the name of a Scottish Highland clan, historically associated with the mountainous district of Kintail in nortwestern Scotland, with Cromarty, and with Loch Seaforth (Loch Shiphoirt) on the Island of Harris."]}]},{"name":"Murdoch","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of <i>Muireadhach</i>, meaning ‘lord’, but said to be a derivative of <i>muir</i> ‘sea’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Murdoch Mackenzie 5th Laird of Kintail was born in 1363, in Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland, his father, Murdoch Dubh Mackenzie 4th Lord of Kintail, was 23 and his mother, Lady Isabel MacAulay of Lochbroom, was 19. He married Finguala MacLeod of Harris about 1395, in Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1416, in his hometown, at the age of 53, and was buried in Ross-shire, Scotland."},"et":{"1363–1416":"1363–1416","1366–Male":"1366–Surnud","1369–Male":"1369–Surnud","1374–1416":"1374–1416","1398–1488":"1398–1488","1340–1375":"1340–1375","1344–1370":"1344–1370","before 1363":"enne 1363","1363":"1363","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","1369":"1369","1488":"1488","1344":"1344","1366":"1366","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","about 1395":"umbes 1395","1416":"1416","Kintail, Highland, Scotland":"Kintail, Highland, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Scotland","Ross-shire, Scotland":"Ross-shire, Scotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1363–1416":"1363–1416","1366–Male":"1366–Kuollut","1369–Male":"1369–Kuollut","1374–1416":"1374–1416","1398–1488":"1398–1488","1340–1375":"1340–1375","1344–1370":"1344–1370","before 1363":"ennen vuotta 1363","1363":"1363","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","1369":"1369","1488":"1488","1344":"1344","1366":"1366","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","about 1395":"noin 1395","1416":"1416","Kintail, Highland, Scotland":"Kintail, Highland, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Scotland","Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Lochbroom, Ross-shire, Scotland","Ross-shire, Scotland":"Ross-shire, Scotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland"},"fr"